report_text: endotracheal tube tip terminates approximately 3 cm from the carina . an enteric tube tip is within the stomach . moderate enlargement of the cardiac silhouette is re- demonstrated . widening of the superior mediastinal contour is likely due to low lung volumes and supine positioning . there is mild pulmonary vascular congestion . moderate to severe enlargement of the pulmonary arteries is re- demonstrated . bibasilar airspace opacities likely
